HEADWORD: Tiler
<hw>Til"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A man whose occupation
is to cover buildings with tiles.</def> <rj><au>Bancroft.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiler</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tiler
<hw>Til"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of uncertain origin, but probably
from E. <ets>tile</ets>, n.]</ety> <def>A doorkeeper or attendant at a
lodge of Freemasons.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>tyler</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilery</ent>⟦br⟧
